identity.name: IdentifierUse
identity.description: Identifier use enumerator. All codes from system http://hl7.org/fhir/identifier-use.

identity.name: Code
identity.description: The code (used as the code in the resource instance). If the code is in italics, this indicates that the code is not selectable ('Abstract')

identity.name: Display
identity.description: The display (used in the display element of a Coding). If there is no display, implementers should not simply display the code, but map the concept into their application

identity.name: Definition
identity.description: An explanation of the meaning of the concept

identity.name: Translations
identity.description: Translation for enum values to different languages.

values: The identifier recommended for display and use in real-world interactions.

The identifier considered to be most trusted for the identification of this item.
An identifier that was assigned in secondary use - it serves to identify the object in a relative context, but cannot be consistently assigned to the same object again in a different context.
